IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION'S MISSION IS TO CARE FOR PEOPLE AND IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF LIFE IN THE COMMUNITIES WE SERVE.
IRS990.MissionDescription: COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION'S MISSION IS TO CARE FOR PEOPLE AND IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF LIFE IN THE COMMUNITIES WE SERVE.

Activity2.Description: THE CORPORATION PROMOTES HEALTHCARE IN SOUTH CENTRAL KENTUCKY BY OWNING AND MANAGING PHYSICIAN PRACTICES AND IMMEDIATE CARE CLINICS. THE PHYSICIAN PRACTICES COVER A WIDE RANGE OF MEDICAL SPECIALTIES, INCLUDING VASCULAR, CARDIOTHORACIC SURGERY, NEUROLOGY, HOSPITALISTS, OBSTETRICS, GYNECOLOGY, RADIOLOGY, PSYCHIATRY AND GENERAL MEDICINE.

Activity3.Description: THE CORPORATION PROMOTES HEALTHCARE IN SOUTH CENTRAL KENTUCKY BY OPERATING A COMPREHENSIVE REHABILITATION FACILITY WHICH OFFERS PHYSICAL, OCCUPATIONAL AND SPEECH THERAPY. IN ADDITION, THE CORPORATION PROVIDES STAFFING FOR THERAPY SERVICES IN A RELATED HOME HEALTH AGENCY, TWO CRITICAL ACCESS HOSPITALS, AND ONE NURSING CARE FACILITY.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: MOST OF THE INCOME RECEIVED BY THE CORPORATION IS EXEMPT FROM TAXATION UNDER SECTION 501(A) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. SOME OF ITS INCOME IS SUBJECT TO TAXATION AS UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME. THE CORPORATION FILES FEDERAL INCOME TAX RETURNS, AS WELL AS AN INCOME TAX RETURN IN KENTUCKY. THE CORPORATION IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO U.S. FEDERAL INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS BY TAX AUTHORITIES FOR YEARS BEFORE 2007. FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD (FASB) ACCOUNTING STANDARDS CODIFICATION TOPIC 740 CLARIFIES THE ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES RECOGNIZED IN A COMPANY'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND PRESCRIBES A RECOGNITION THRESHOLD AND MEASUREMENT ATTRIBUTE FOR THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT RECOGNITION AND MEASUREMENT OF A TAX POSITION TAKEN, OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN IN A TAX RETURN. TOPIC 740 ALSO PROVIDES GUIDANCE ON DESCRIPTION, CLASSIFICATION, INTEREST AND PENALTIES, ACCOUNTING IN INTERIM PERIODS, DISCLOSURE AND TRANSITION. THE CORPORATION DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS RECOGNIZED FOR 2010 OR 2009. THE CORPORATION'S PRACTICE IS TO RECOGNIZE INTEREST AND/OR PENALTIES RELATED TO INCOME TAX MATTERS IN INCOME TAX EXPENSE.

Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Explanation: COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION, INC. IS FREQUENTLY ASKED TO CONTRIBUTE TO A VARIETY OF ORGANIZATIONS AND FUNDRAISING PROJECTS. COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION, INC. WAS ESTABLISHED TO SUPPORT THE HEALTHCARE MISSIONS OF THE BOWLING GREEN WARREN COUNTY COMMUNITY HOSPITAL CORPORATION AND OTHER NON-PROFIT AFFILIATES OF COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION. IT IS COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION'S GOAL TO BE A SUPPORTIVE CITIZEN AND, WHEN PRACTICAL AND POSSIBLE, TO MAKE REASONABLE CONTRIBUTIONS WHICH ARE BENEFICIAL TO THE COMMUNITY AND PARALLEL TO OUR EXEMPT PURPOSE.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: DESCRIPTION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S ACTIVITIES COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION ("CHC") PROMOTES HEALTH CARE IN SOUTH CENTRAL KENTUCKY THROUGH ITS SUPPORT OF THE BOWLING GREEN WARREN COUNTY COMMUNITY HOSPITAL CORPORATION DBA THE MEDICAL CENTER (WHICH HAS CAMPUSES IN BOWLING GREEN AND SCOTTSVILLE, KY), THE MEDICAL CENTER AT FRANKLIN, COMMONWEALTH REGIONAL SPECIALTY HOSPITAL, AND OTHER AFFILIATED TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATIONS AND PROGRAMS. IN FULFILLING ITS MISSION, CHC DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY SPONSORS OR PARTICIPATES IN THE FOLLOWING ACTIVITIES: OVERVIEW OF SPECIFIC AREAS THE COMMONWEALTH HEALTH FREE CLINIC, INC. ("FREE CLINIC") IS A SECTION 501(C)(3) ORGANIZATION THAT PROVIDES COMPLETELY FREE BASIC MEDICAL AND DENTAL DIAGNOSTIC AND TREATMENT SERVICES FOR THOSE QUALIFYING INDIVIDUALS WITH NO INSURANCE AND NO ABILITY TO PAY. ELDERLY INDIVIDUALS ALSO QUALIFY FOR PRESCRIPTIONS. MANY PHYSICIANS AND DENTISTS DONATE THEIR TIME AND CHC PROVIDES A FULL TIME ADMINISTRATOR. FURTHERMORE, PHARMACEUTICAL COMPANIES, THEIR REPRESENTATIVES, OTHER MEDICAL SUPPLIERS, AND PHYSICIANS ALSO PROVIDE FREE PRESCRIPTION DRUGS AND OTHER NEEDED ITEMS FOR DISTRIBUTION TO PATIENTS. FROM THE BEGINNING, CHC AND THE MEDICAL CENTER MADE A COMMITMENT TO BE NOT ONLY AN EXCELLENT MEDICAL FACILITY BUT ALSO THE PREEMINENT RESOURCE FOR HEALTH CARE INFORMATION IN WESTERN AND SOUTH CENTRAL KENTUCKY. THIS PHILOSOPHY GAVE BIRTH TO THE THE MEDICAL CENTER'S COMMUNITY WELLNESS PROGRAM. THIS PROGRAM PROVIDES FREE EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS TO THE COMMUNITY AND WORK SITES ON PREVENTION, WELLNESS, HEALTH, LIFESTYLE AND DISEASE MANAGEMENT. CHC AND THE MEDICAL CENTER SPONSOR THE HEALTH AND WELLNESS CENTER ("CENTER") IN THE GREENWOOD MALL IN BOWLING GREEN, KENTUCKY. THE CENTER PROVIDES FREE HEALTH EDUCATION SERVICES TO THE COMMUNITY AND IS STAFFED BY REGISTERED NURSES WHO ANSWER QUESTIONS, ASSIST WITH FREE HEALTH SCREENINGS AND COORDINATE OTHER ACTIVITIES. EACH MONTH THE CENTER FEATURES A DIFFERENT FREE SCREENING SUCH AS CHOLESTEROL, GLUCOSE, DEPRESSION, HEARING, OR PULMONARY FUNCTION. PRESENTATIONS AND PROGRAMS ARE PROVIDED DURING THE WEEK BY A VARIETY OF HEALTHCARE PROVIDERS. SUPPORT GROUPS ALSO MEET AT THE CENTER. ANNUALLY, CHC AND ITS CORPORATE AFFILIATES PROMOTE PARTICIPATION IN THE AMERICAN CANCER SOCIETY'S RELAY FOR LIFE PROGRAM AND THE AMERICAN HEART ASSOCIATION'S HEART WALK. IN ADDITION, CHC AND THE MEDICAL CENTER ENCOURAGE PHYSICAL ACTIVITY BY SPONSORING THE MEDICAL CENTER 10K CLASSIC AND CHILDREN'S CLASSIC, EVENTS WHICH COMBINE SEPARATE ACTIVITIES FOR THOSE WHO WANT TO WALK OR RUN COMPETITIVELY. ANNUALLY, OVER 2,000 INDIVIDUALS PARTICIPATE IN THE 10K AND CHILDREN'S CLASSIC EVENTS. ANNUALLY, CHC AND THE MEDICAL CENTER SPONSOR A COMMUNITY-WIDE HEALTH AND WELLNESS EXPO AT A LOCAL CONVENTION CENTER. THIS EVENT PROVIDES VARIOUS HEALTH SCREENINGS AND OFFERS CITIZENS CONCENTRATED ACCESS TO BOTH INFORMATION REGARDING MANY COMMUNITY HEALTHCARE RESOURCES AND TO THE STAFF WHO WORK WITH THESE COMMUNITY HEALTHCARE AGENCIES. CHC AND THE MEDICAL CENTER'S SENIOR HEALTH CARE NETWORK PROVIDE FREE WEEKLY EXERCISE PROGRAMS TO MEET THE SPECIFIC NEEDS OF PEOPLE OVER 55. THE CLASSES ARE OFFERED IN VARIOUS LOCATIONS. A PERSONAL ADVISOR ASSISTS SENIOR CITIZENS IN FILLING OUT MEDICARE AND OTHER INSURANCE FORMS. FREE HEALTH SCREENINGS CHECKING BLOOD PRESSURE, BLOOD SUGAR LEVELS, CHOLESTEROL AND MORE ARE PROVIDED TWICE PER MONTH IN BOWLING GREEN AND SURROUNDING COUNTIES. CHC AND THE MEDICAL CENTER SPONSOR THE WOMEN'S CENTER WHICH PROVIDES FOR THE SPECIAL NEEDS OF WOMEN INCLUDING HEALTHCARE SERVICES, PERSONAL EDUCATION ON SELF-EXAMINATIONS, EXERCISE AND NUTRITION, A LUNCHEON SERVICE ON WOMEN'S HEALTH AND PROFESSIONAL CONCERNS, AND A NEWSLETTER. IN ADDITION, CHC AND THE MEDICAL CENTER SPONSOR THE MEN'S HEALTH ALLIANCE WHICH OFFERS MEMBERS A VARIETY OF HEALTH-RELATED BENEFITS INCLUDING ANNUAL HEALTH SCREENINGS. WITH THE SUPPORT OF CHC, THE MEDICAL CENTER IS WELL EQUIPPED FOR THE MOST COMMON CARDIAC PROBLEMS INCLUDING THE ABILITY TO PERFORM CARDIAC CATHETERIZATIONS, OPEN HEART SURGERY AND TO PROVIDE CARDIAC REHABILITATION. THE MEDICAL CENTER ALSO OFFERS CHEMOTHERAPY AND DIAGNOSTIC RADIOGRAPHY FOR CANCER SCREENING AND TREATMENT. OTHER SERVICES THAT CAN BE PROVIDED ON AN OUTPATIENT BASIS INCLUDE: EEG/EMG, EKG, ENDOSCOPY, IV THERAPY, DIGITAL MAMMOGRAPHY, NUCLEAR MEDICINE, PHYSICAL THERAPY, RADIOLOGY (CT, ULTRASOUND) RESPIRATORY THERAPY AND VASCULAR STUDIES. CHC'S CONTRIBUTION TO OUR COMMUNITIES DISPLAYED BELOW IS A DETAILED LIST OF HOW OVER $50.4 MILLION IN BENEFITS WERE PROVIDED DIRECTLY TO THE COMMUNITY BY COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION AND ITS AFFILIATES INCLUDING: THE MEDICAL CENTER (BOWLING GREEN AND SCOTTSVILLE CAMPUSES), THE MEDICAL CENTER AT FRANKLIN, COMMONWEALTH HEALTH FREE CLINIC, AND COMMONWEALTH REGIONAL SPECIALTY HOSPITAL: CHARITY CARE (FREE OR DISCOUNTED CARE FOR UNINSURED PEOPLE WHOSE INCOMES MET CERTAIN POVERTY GUIDELINES): $10,880,688 UNPAID COST OF MEDICAID: $5,822,198 HEALTH PROFESSIONAL EDUCATION (SCHOLARSHIPS AND FUNDING FOR EDUCATION): $3,276,212 COMMUNITY HEALTH SERVICES (INCLUDES THE COMMONWEALTH FREE CLINIC, FREE COMMUNITY FAIRS, SCREENINGS, PATIENT EDUCATION CLASSES AND HEALTH AND WELLNESS PROJECTS): $4,356,193 SUBSIDIZED HEALTH SERVICES (INCLUDES EMERGENCY CARE AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES FOR WHICH REIMBURSEMENTS DO NOT COVER THE FULL COST AND KENTUCKY PROVIDER TAX TO FUND CARE): $5,274,668 FINANCIAL AND IN-KIND DONATIONS: $132,910 UNPAID COST OF MEDICARE: $15,673,182 BAD DEBT (SERVICES PROVIDED IN WHICH PAYMENT IS EXPECTED, BUT NEVER RECEIVED, STATED AT COST): $4,952,913 COMMUNITY ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT: $107,020 TOTAL CHC COMMUNITY BENEFIT: $50,475,984

THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS OF COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION ARE AUDITED ON A CONSOLIDATED BASIS BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM. UPON CONCLUSION OF THE AUDIT, A REPORT IS PREPARED AND PUBLISHED IN ACCORDANCE WITH GAAP.

FORM 990 IS PLACED ELECTRONICALLY ON A COMPANY WEBSITE USED TO SHARE INFORMATION WITH BOARD MEMBERS. EACH BOARD MEMBER IS PROVIDED ACCESS TO THIS WEBSITE AND IS ASKED TO REVIEW FORM 990 PRIOR TO A DESIGNATED DATE ON WHICH THE RETURN WILL BE FILED. AT LEAST TWO WEEKS OF ADVANCE NOTICE IS GIVEN TO BOARD MEMBERS SO THEY MAY REVIEW THE RETURN.

THE COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION (CHC) (APPLICABLE TO THE CORPORATION AND /OR ITS AFFILIATES) CODE OF CONDUCT EXPLICITLY STATES MEMBERS OF THE BOARD, ADMINISTRATION, THE MEDICAL STAFF AND ALL EMPLOYEES ARE EXPECTED TO AVOID CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. FURTHER, IT REQUIRES DISCLOSURE OF ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST IN A TIMELY MANNER. ALL INDIVIDUALS SIGN AN ACKNOWLEDGEMENT UPON EMPLOYMENT THAT THEY HAVE RECEIVED A COPY OF THE CODE OF CONDUCT, ARE FAMILIAR WITH ITS CONTENT AND UNDERSTAND THEIR RESPONSIBILITIES TO AVOID NON-COMPLIANT ACTIVITY. CHC'S REGULATORY COMPLIANCE COMMITTEE (RCC) REVIEWS AND APPROVES ALL CONTRACTS FOR CHC AND/OR ITS AFFILIATES. THE REVIEW IS DESIGNED TO IDENTIFY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST BY BOARD MEMBERS AND/OR OFFICERS. RCC MEMBERS ARE PROHIBITED FROM TAKING PART IN DECISION REGARDING TRANSACTIONS WITH WHICH HE/SHE HAS A CONFLICT OF INTEREST. ANNUALLY, WRITTEN INQUIRY IS MADE - BY QUESTIONNAIRE - OF BOARD MEMBERS AND OFFICERS SEEKING DISCLOSURE OF CONFLICTS OF INTEREST OR INFORMATION THAT RELATES TO FAMILY MEMBERS. TRANSACTIONS ARISING ARE REVIEWED BY MANAGEMENT AS THEY OCCUR.

COMPENSATION FOR THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER IS SET BY THE REGULATORY COMPLIANCE COMMITTEE (RCC) OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. COMPENSATION FOR OFFICERS OF THE CORPORATION IS REVIEWED BY THE SAME COMMITTEE. THE RCC RETAINS AN INDEPENDENT CONSULTANT TO CONDUCT AN ANNUAL SURVEY OF COMPENSATION FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS IN THE HEALTHCARE INDUSTRY AND USES ITS REPORT IN ITS COMPENSATION DECISION.
DOCUMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE IF REQUIRED, AND IN THE MANNER REQUIRED, BY THE GOVERNING AGENCY OR BOND AUTHORITY.
JOHN DESMARAIS SERVES AS PRESIDENT AND CEO OF COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION ("CHC"). MR. DESMARAIS' WIFE, CHRIS DESMARAIS, IS EMPLOYED BY CHC AS SENIOR VICE PRESIDENT OF QUALITY.

COMMONWEALTH HEALTH CORPORATION ("CHC') WORKS TO FULLFILL ITS MISSION OF CARING FOR PEOPLE AND IMPROVING THE QUALITY OF LIFE IN THE COMMUNITIES IT SERVES THROUGH ITS SUPPORT OF THE BOWLING GREEN WARREN COUNTY COMMUNITY HOSPITAL CORPORATION DBA THE MEDICAL CENTER ("THE MEDICAL CENTER"), A GENERAL ACUTE CARE HOSPITAL LICENSED FOR 330 BEDS IN BOWLING GREEN, KENTUCKY. IN ADDITION, THE MEDICAL CENTER OWNS AND OPERATES AN AMBULANCE SERVICE SERVING WARREN COUNTY, KENTUCKY, A RETAIL PHARMACY IN BOWLING GREEN, KENTUCKY, AND A 25-BED CRITICAL ACCESS HOSPITAL (THE MEDICAL CENTER AT SCOTTSVILLE) AND 110-BED NURSING CARE UNIT IN SCOTTSVILLE, KENTUCKY. IN ADDITION, CHC PROMOTES HEALTHCARE THROUGH ITS SUPPORT OF THE MEDICAL CENTER AT FRANKLIN, INC., A 25-BED CRITICAL ACCESS HOSPITAL IN FRANKLIN, KENTUCKY, AND COMMONWEALTH REGIONAL SPECIALTY HOSPITAL, INC. A 28-BED LONG-TERM CARE ACUTE CARE HOSPITAL LOCATED WITHIN THE MEDICAL CENTER. OTHER SERVICES SUPPORTED BY CHC INCLUDE THE COMMONWEALTH HEALTH FREE CLINIC, INC. AND THE COMMONWEALTH HEALTH FOUNDATION. PLEASE SEE SCHEDULE O FOR MORE INFORMATION.
